Here's the recommended structure:

**1. Make HTTP calls injectable**

```csharp
// In your MCP server project
public class MyTool
{
    private readonly HttpClient _httpClient;

    public MyTool(HttpClient httpClient)
    {
        _httpClient = httpClient;
    }

    public async Task<string> GetDataAsync(string id)
    {
        var response = await _httpClient.GetAsync($"https://api.example.com/data/{id}");
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
    }
}
```

**2. Create the test project**

```bash
dotnet new xunit -n MyMcpServer.Tests
cd MyMcpServer.Tests
dotnet add reference ../MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj
dotnet add package Moq            # optional, for other interfaces
dotnet add package RichardSzalay.MockHttp  # mock HttpClient
```

**3. Use `MockHttpMessageHandler` to fake API responses**

```csharp
using RichardSzalay.MockHttp;
using Xunit;

public class MyToolTests
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task GetDataAsync_ReturnsExpectedPayload()
    {
        // Arrange — fake the external API
        var mockHttp = new MockHttpMessageHandler();
        mockHttp
            .When("https://api.example.com/data/42")
            .Respond("application/json", """{"name":"test"}""");

        var httpClient = mockHttp.ToHttpClient();
        var tool = new MyTool(httpClient);

        // Act
        var result = await tool.GetDataAsync("42");

        // Assert
        Assert.Contains("test", result);
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task GetDataAsync_ThrowsOnServerError()
    {
        var mockHttp = new MockHttpMessageHandler();
        mockHttp
            .When("https://api.example.com/data/*")
            .Respond(System.Net.HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError);

        var tool = new MyTool(mockHttp.ToHttpClient());

        await Assert.ThrowsAsync<HttpRequestException>(
            () => tool.GetDataAsync("99"));
    }
}
```

**Key principles:**

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **HTTP calls** | Inject `HttpClient`; mock via `MockHttpMessageHandler` |
| **Other services** | Define interfaces, mock with Moq/NSubstitute |
| **Project layout** | `src/MyMcpServer/` + `tests/MyMcpServer.Tests/` |
| **Test runner** | xUnit (or NUnit/MSTest — all work fine) |

This lets you test every tool's logic — success paths, error handling, deserialization — without any real network calls.
